description: Starts an asynchronous job that runs an existing dashboard schedule and sends the dashboard snapshot through email. Only one job can run simultaneously in a given schedule. Repeated requests are skipped with a 202 HTTP status code. For more information, see Scheduling and sending Amazon QuickSight reports by email and Configuring email report settings for a Amazon QuickSight dashboard in the Amazon QuickSight User Guide.

parameters.name: AwsAccountId
parameters.description: The ID of the Amazon Web Services account that the dashboard snapshot job is executed in.

parameters.name: DashboardId
parameters.description: The ID of the dashboard that you want to start a snapshot job schedule for.

parameters.name: ScheduleId
parameters.description: The ID of the schedule that you want to start a snapshot job schedule for. The schedule ID can be found in the Amazon QuickSight console in the Schedules pane of the dashboard that the schedule is configured for.

nested_items.name: RequestId
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services request ID for this operation.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The HTTP status of the request.
